# CODEOWNERS — sample. Copy to .github/CODEOWNERS in the target repo.
#
# This enforces review on the files that set the rules. Anyone changing CI, the agent
# instructions or governance must get the named owner's review before the PR can merge.
# It only takes effect once branch protection requires review from code owners.
#
# Replace @PLACEHOLDER-owner with the real owner handle (Clent). Least privilege:
# name the smallest set of owners that must approve, not the whole team.

# The workflows and settings that run and gate everything else.
/.github/                 @PLACEHOLDER-owner   # PLACEHOLDER — set to Clent's GitHub handle

# Agent instructions — these steer what the agents do.
/AGENTS.md                @PLACEHOLDER-owner   # PLACEHOLDER — set to Clent's GitHub handle
/CLAUDE.md                @PLACEHOLDER-owner   # PLACEHOLDER — set to Clent's GitHub handle

# Governance — the rules of the road.
/00-governance/           @PLACEHOLDER-owner   # PLACEHOLDER — set to Clent's GitHub handle
/governance/              @PLACEHOLDER-owner   # PLACEHOLDER — remove if the repo has no /governance
